opted to not go into it at the very beginning, I

01:42.525 --> 01:51.493
suppose, because we wanted to We were satisfied. 
We had a system which was working well, although it

01:52.993 --> 01:57.239
was a little bit cumbersome, but it was working 
well. And we decided to let it wait a while. And I

02:00.784 --> 02:08.994
don't recall the time, but it seemed like around 
1985 was probably when we started the SYMS system

02:00.784 --> 02:08.994
at that time. And we, at that time, visited a number 
of vendors, and it was interesting to see their

02:09.095 --> 02:19.168
proposals and programs and everything. got the 
operation. It took us about a year to really get the

02:20.577 --> 02:26.306
programming and everything done. It was a major 
undertaking, but really well planned through the

02:26.346 --> 02:37.223
computer system, computer department, I guess it 
was. And we had great cooperation and everything,

02:37.243 --> 02:44.054
and it worked, as I recall, really fairly well from 
the very beginning. I don't think we had many

02:44.114 --> 02:46.438
hitches because we had planned and worked so hard 
on it and laying good foundation with it. Were

02:50.461 --> 02:55.868
there any heroes or heroines that were supporters 
of that decision to bring it about? Anybody that

02:57.009 --> 02:59.572
deserves a pat on the back for supporting it? Oh, I 
suppose, and for the life of me right now, I can't

03:02.095 --> 03:13.388
remember who

