16:21.719 --> 16:23.241
decision on that. When you were getting down to the 
decision on those marginal admits, Did you want

16:31.370 --> 16:33.432
there to be a face-to-face? Well, yeah, I always 
wanted to. There was not always that. I realize

16:38.336 --> 16:40.058
sometimes distance would... Right. But I always 
wanted a kid to come in, and I could talk to him

16:40.638 --> 16:50.127
man-to-man, man-to-woman, whatever the case may 
be on the thing. It helped when you can talk to them,

16:50.347 --> 16:52.329
I think. It gives them a chance to present their 
side of the story. A lot of times, I thought the best

16:55.752 --> 16:59.956
decision was, no, not now. Mm-hmm. But again, the 
philosophy was we're not denying you admission to

17:00.698 --> 17:07.147
A&M. We're trying to give you a route that you can 
graduate from A&M. And I think as long as we used

17:11.573 --> 17:20.504
that, for the most part, the students left 
reasonably satisfied. Obviously, they wanted to

17:20.525 --> 17:23.909
come or they wouldn't have made the effort to even 
come for an interview. But that's the philosophy

17:24.870 --> 17:29.136
we tried to follow. What else should we, have we 
left anything out that we should have covered? I

17:33.544 --> 17:35.266
don't know of anything. I think we've covered a 
whole lot more than I thought we were going to.

